✅ Fix 3: Keep AddressDetailsDTO Only for Response

Modify AddressDetailsDTO so it remains strict for responses.

import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;
import lombok.Data;

@Data
public class AddressDetailsDTO {
    @NotNull(message = "CharacterSetType must not be null in response")
    private CharacterSetType characterSetType;
    
    private String postalCode;
    private String country;
    private String prefecture;
    private String city;
    private String town;
    private String lane;
}

	•	This ensures that when an address is returned, characterSetType is always set.
	•	The search request does not enforce this since it’s a different DTO.

